Date: Wed, 7 Feb 2024 20:01:36 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] Speed optimization with insignificant impact on image
 quality: (#1165)

use wxIMAGE_QUALITY_BILINEAR which is less CPU intensive than using
wxIMAGE_QUALITY_HIGH, but is hardly noticeable. At the same time
the fix ensures that hot pixels won't look like stars.

Signed-off-by: Leo Shatz <leonid.shatz@gmail.com>
---
 guider.cpp | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/guider.cpp b/guider.cpp
index c9487ed56..c82d826d8 100644
--- a/guider.cpp
+++ b/guider.cpp
@@ -487,7 +487,7 @@ bool Guider::PaintHelper(wxAutoBufferedPaintDCBase& dc, wxMemoryDC& memDC)
 
                     if (newWidth > 0 && newHeight > 0)
                     {
-                        m_displayedImage->Rescale(newWidth, newHeight, wxIMAGE_QUALITY_HIGH);
+                        m_displayedImage->Rescale(newWidth, newHeight, wxIMAGE_QUALITY_BILINEAR);
                     }
                 }
             }
